EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 022300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 975 WILL BE CENTRED OVER NERN
ENGLAND. THIS LOW SHOULD DRIFT SLWY SWARDS TO BECOME CENTRED ACROSS THE ENGLISH
CHANNEL BY SATURDAY EVENING. BY THIS TIME ANOTHER WEAKER AREA OF LOW PRESSURE
MAY DEVELOP ACROSS EERN SCOTLAND ALTHOUGH THIS LOW IS NOT LIKELY TO BE AS
COHERENT SO WILL LIKELY WEAKEN FURTHER AS THE ORIGINAL LOW PUSHES FURTHER
AWAY INTO FRANCE. DESPITE THIS WE MAINTAIN A TROUGH ACROSS MUCH OF WERN CULLERCOATS
DURING THE WEEKEND WITH A WEAK RIDGE PUSHING IN FM THE E. THE RIDGE WILL
THEN CROSS CULLERCOATS DURING SUNDAY NIGHT AND EARLY MONDAY BEFORE ANOTHER
AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 990 MOVS UP FM THE LOW COUNTRIES BY MONDAY AFTERNOON.
STRG TO GALE FORCE WINDS ARE LIKELY TO AFFECT MUCH OF CULLERCOATS THROUGH
FRIDAY EVENING BEFORE EASING BY SATURDAY MORNING. MOSTLY NON-HAZARDOUS WINDS
ARE THEN EXP BUT BY THE END OF THE PERIOD GALES MAY BEGIN TO DEVELOP AGAIN
